
1- Collection

create 5 li tags
First Item
Second Item...etc

ul give a class of collection
li class collection-item


2-Collection as Links

create a div give it a class of collection with 4 links with class of collection-item.

--BADGES--

Badges are inside a span

Inside the same div create two a tags and give them a class of collection-item
and inside the a tag create and span with one: class badge, value of a tag equal to 44 and inside the other a tag a span with class badge new and value of 3 for the span and Six item for the a tag.

<a href="#" class="collection-item">
    <span class="badge">44</span>Fith Item</a>
<a href="#" class-"collection-item">
    <span class="badge new">3</span>Sixth item</a>

3-Collection with header

-create an ul with fourth items having as childrem Item One, Item Two...

-ul give it a class of collection with-header

-put a h4 after the first item of the list

4-Secondary content

-create this structure:

Copy all and start with the firt item giving this classes:

ul collection with-header
first li collection-header and inside this li an h4 tag witht the header you want
the next li give the class of collection-item and the a tag inside the class of
secondary-content, and use the icon from material-icons of type close.

 <!-- SECONDARY CONTENT -->
    <ul>
      <li>
        <h4>Items</h4>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div>First Item
          <a href="#">
            <i>/i>
          </a>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>


